{"type":"message","id":"04004c55","parentId":"60eea455","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:18:22.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I removed that task. Now I need to check what's causing the \"Delivering to Feishu requires target\" error even though we set channel to \"webchat\". Let me look at the task configurations more carefully.\n\nActually, I notice that even though we set \"channel\": \"webchat\", the error says \"Delivering to Feishu\". This suggests that maybe the channel setting isn't being applied correctly, or there's some other issue.\n\nWait - looking at the error again: \"Unknown target 'Sir' for Feishu\". This sounds like the task payload itself is trying to send to \"Sir\" as a name, rather than using the configured delivery channel.\n\nThe issue might be that the agent payload itself says \"åéįŧįĻæ·\" (send to user) but doesn't know who \"įĻæ·\" is, so it's trying to use \"Sir\" as a target.\n\nLet me check if maybe I need to add a specific \"to\" field with the user's open_id for the webchat delivery to work properly.\n\nActually, looking at the config more carefully - I set \"channel\": \"webchat\" but didn't add a \"to\" field. For webchat, maybe I need to specify the target differently, or maybe the issue is that these isolated session tasks are trying to deliver to the user but don't have the right context.\n\nLet me try adding the user's open_id to the delivery config.","thinkingSignature":"9fc5070c7db77cc0aadc76697152519eae8b0cb2288d4dc038e6731151576c42"},{"type":"text","text":"éŪéĒæŊåģä―ŋčŪūį―Ūäš webchat æļ éïžä― delivery åŊč―čŋéčĶæåŪįŪæ ãčŪĐæäŋŪåĪčŋäšäŧŧåĄïž\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oyu0vf4p17xi_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","id":"5071638d-65c3-4709-a509-3fddb9b5a2d6","patch":{"delivery":{"channel":"webchat","mode":"announce","to":"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389"}}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","mode