{"type":"message","id":"150ffe9c","parentId":"1d51104b","timestamp":"2026-03-19T05:30:42.660Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v0fdhcv60hxx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\r\nname: Proactivity (Proactive Agent)\r\nslug: proactivity\r\nversion: 1.0.1\r\nhomepage: https://clawic.com/skills/proactivity\r\ndescription: Anticipates needs, keeps work moving, and improves through use so the agent gets more proactive over time.\r\nchangelog: \"Strengthens proactive behavior with reverse prompting, self-healing, working-buffer recovery, and clearer SOUL and AGENTS setup.\"\r\nmetadata: {\"clawdbot\":{\"emoji\":\"âĄ\",\"requires\":{\"bins\":[]},\"os\":[\"linux\",\"darwin\",\"win32\"],\"configPaths\":[\"~/proactivity/\"],\"configPaths.optional\":[\"./AGENTS.md\",\"./TOOLS.md\",\"./SOUL.md\",\"./HEARTBEAT.md\"]}}\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Architecture\r\n\r\nProactive state lives in `~/proactivity/` and separates durable boundaries from active work. If that folder is missing or empty, run `setup.md`.\r\n\r\n```\r\n~/proactivity/\r\nâââ memory.md                 # Stable activation and boundary rules\r\nâââ session-state.md          # Current task, last decision, next move\r\nâââ heartbeat.md              # Lightweight recurring checks\r\nâââ patterns.md               # Reusable proactive moves that worked\r\nâââ log.md                    # Recent proactive actions and outcomes\r\nâââ domains/                  # Domain-specific overrides\r\nâââ memory/\r\n    âââ working-buffer.md     # Volatile breadcrumbs for long tasks\r\n```\r\n\r\n## When to Use\r\n\r\nUse when the user wants the agent to think ahead, anticipate needs, keep momentum without waiting for prompts, recover context fast, and follow through like a strong operator.\r\n\r\n\n[107 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773898242635}}
