{"type":"message","id":"b620a10e","parentId":"65513e22","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:59:25.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is running. The startup script is in place. The user is asking why it doesn't auto-restart when they exit - I think they mean when the Gateway stops or when they log off/login.\n\nThe startup script is set up to run at login via the Windows Startup folder. This should work when the user logs into Windows.\n\nIf it's not working, possible reasons:\n1. The Startup folder path might be wrong\n2. The script might need admin privileges to run\n3. There might be a security setting preventing .cmd files from running at startup\n\nLet me explain this to the user and ask for more details about what they mean by \"exit\".","thinkingSignature":"6f6b1f9e6df43a939299b3b1da8196c4ca985691384ddf71406e18f7fd693721"},{"type":"text","text":"åŊåĻčæŽå·ēéį―ŪåĨ―ïž\n\n```\nä―į―Ū: C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup\\OpenClaw\\gateway.cmd\n```\n\n**čŋäļŠčæŽäžåĻä― įŧå― Windows æķčŠåĻčŋčĄã**\n\nä― čŊī\"æŊæŽĄéåšįæķå\"ïžå·ä―æŊæïž\n1. **æģĻé/éæ°įŧå― Windows** æķïž\n2. ** Gateway æåĪåæ­Ē** æķïž\n3. **įĩčéåŊ** æķïž\n\nåĶææŊįĩčéåŊæįŧå―åæēĄåŊåĻïžåŊč―éčĶïž\n- æĢæĨ Windows åŊåĻæäŧķåĪđæŊåĶįæ\n- æä―ŋįĻčŪĄåäŧŧåĄä―äļšåĪįĻæđæĄ\n\nä― į°åĻéå°įæŊåŠį§æåĩïž"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":96297,"output":259,"cacheRead":38475,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135031,"cost":{"input":0.028889099999999997,"output":0.00031079999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00115425,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030354149999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773903558924}}
