{"type":"message","id":"555e53bd","parentId":"6e3b2e54","timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:04:35.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is running. The issue is that the watchdog script uses Invoke-WebRequest to check the gateway, but it's returning an error even when the gateway is running. This is because the gateway doesn't respond to HTTP GET requests at the root URL.\n\nLet me fix the watchdog script to use a better check method - maybe using Test-NetConnection or checking if the port is listening.\n\nActually, the better approach is to use `Test-NetConnection` or check the RPC probe directly.","thinkingSignature":"0c12ac0b04b891ea8dfa83917f14a97eb594c294d5ffd6ffba20f5b9c42be2c6"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway æ­ĢåĻčŋčĄãéŪéĒæŊ watchdog æĢæĩæđåžäļåŊđ - Gateway įæ đč·Ŋåūäļååš HTTP GETãčŪĐæäŋŪåĪæĢæĩéŧčūïž\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w89th31v2wr8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# OpenClaw Gateway Watchdog\n# čŠåĻįæ§ Gateway čŋįĻïžåĶæåæ­ĒåčŠåĻéåŊ\n\n$GatewayPort = 18789\n$CheckInterval = 30\n$LogDir = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\logs\"\n$LogFile = \"$LogDir\\gateway-watchdog.log\"\n\n# Create log directory if not exists\nif (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $LogDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Message)\n    $Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    $LogMessage = \"$Timestamp $Message\"\n    Add-Content -Path $LogFile -Value $LogMessage -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    Write-Host $LogMessage\n}\n\nfunction Test-GatewayRunning {\n    try {\n        $TCPClient = New-Object System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient\n        $TCPClient.Connect(\"127.0.0.1\", $GatewayPort)\n        $TCPClient.Close()\n        return $true\n    } catch {\n        return $false\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Log \"=== Gateway Watchdog Started ===\"\n\nwhile ($true) {\n    if (Test-GatewayRunning) {\n   