{"type":"message","id":"e659b3c9","parentId":"a3fce6f9","timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:45:13.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that when they try to start OpenClaw automatically (probably through the startup folder or scheduled task), the `opendaw.ps1` file (they probably meant `gateway-watchdog.ps1`) is being opened in Notepad instead of being executed.\n\nThis is a common Windows issue - `.ps1` files are associated with Notepad by default for some users, or the script is being treated as a text file rather than an executable.\n\nThe solution is to:\n1. Change the scheduled task to run the PowerShell interpreter explicitly with the script as an argument (which we're already doing)\n2. Or change the file association for .ps1 files\n3. Or use a .bat file to call PowerShell (which we already have with start-watchdog.bat)\n\nLet me check the scheduled task to see how it's configured.","thinkingSignature":"725c944ef6ec906e9356a40bacab921980c9efeaf71e16be99185faae7b0d0df"},{"type":"text","text":"čŋæŊ Windows æ `.ps1` æäŧķå―æææŽæäŧķæåžäšãčŪĐææĢæĨčŪĄåäŧŧåĄįéį―Ūïž\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jxxqf9myla6c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"schtasks /query /tn \"OpenClaw Gateway Watchdog\" /fo csv /v 2>&1 | findstr \"Task to run\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":159,"output":245,"cacheRead":148599,"cacheWrite":993,"totalTokens":149996,"cost":{"input":0.0000636,"output":0.0003675,"cacheRead":0.00594396,"cacheWrite":0.00014895,"total":0.00652401}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773920703156}}
